                            <comment id="457911" author="zam" created="Wed, 28 May 2025 17:27:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The root cause is that lfs migrate tries to convert the dir in cb_migrate_mdt_fini():&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* dir migration finished, shrink its stripes */&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; cb_migrate_mdt_fini(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; *path, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; p, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; *dp, void *data,
                               struct dirent64 *de)
{
        struct find_param *param = data;
        struct lmv_user_md *lmu = param-&amp;gt;fp_lmv_md;
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; lmulen = lmv_user_md_size(lmu-&amp;gt;lum_stripe_count, lmu-&amp;gt;lum_magic);
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; ret = 0;

        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (de &amp;amp;&amp;amp; de-&amp;gt;d_type != DT_DIR)
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;goto&lt;/span&gt; out;

        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (*dp != -1) {
                /*
                 * close it before setxattr because the latter may destroy the
                 * original object, and cause close fail.
                 */
                ret = close(*dp);
                *dp = -1;
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ret)
                        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;goto&lt;/span&gt; out;
        }

        ret = setxattr(path, XATTR_NAME_LMV, lmu, lmulen, 0);
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ret == -EALREADY)
                ret = 0;
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;by invoking setxattr() syscall for a xattr in &quot;trusted&quot; namespace.  The syscall fails because Linux doesn&apos;t allow a non-root user (user w/o CAP_SYS_ADMIN) to access any xattr from the &quot;trusted&quot; namespace:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;
xattr_permission(struct inode *inode, &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; *name, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; mask)
{
   ...
        /*
         * The trusted.* namespace can only be accessed by privileged users.
         */
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!strncmp(name, XATTR_TRUSTED_PREFIX, XATTR_TRUSTED_PREFIX_LEN)) {
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!capable(CAP_SYS_ADMIN))
                        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; (mask &amp;amp; MAY_WRITE) ? -EPERM : -ENODATA;
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; 0;
        }
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;moreover, it fails silently, as the error from the setxattr() call is ignored.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
